sage percentage (45%)\n- Progress bar visualization\n- Source: existing token tracking from StatusBar\n\n### 2. Activated MCP\n- List of connected MCP servers\n- Status indicator: ● connected (green), ○ disconnected (muted)\n- Shows server name only (not individual tools)\n- Source: MCPToolManager or equivalent\n\n### 3. Modified Files\n- Files created (+), modified (~), or touched (•) during session\n- Automatic tracking via tool call events (EditFile, WriteFile, etc.)\n- Scrollable if list exceeds available space\n- Color coding:\n  - `+` green: created\n  - `~` amber: modified\n  - `•` muted: touched/read\n\n### 4. Bottom Info (Footer)\n- Project path with branch: `~/REPOS/agent-tui:main`\n- Uses `~` for home directory\n- CLI name and version: `agent-tui v1.2.3`\n- Separated by 1px border-top\n\n---\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### Widget\nCreate new `InfoPanel` widget in `entrypoints/widgets/` extending `Static`.\n\n### Layout Integration\n- Add to `app.py` `compose()` alongside existing widgets\n- Use `dock: right` to position\n- Toggle visibility via Ctrl+M binding (reuse `toggle_mcp_panel` or new)\n- Auto-hide logic on terminal resize event\n\n### File Tracking\n- Hook into existing tool call events\n- Track files from: `EditFile`, `WriteFile`, `CreateFile`, `ReadFile` tools\n- Maintain in-memory list during session\n- Clear on new session\n\n### State Management\n- Reactive properties for each section\n- Updates flow from existing app state (tokens, MCP servers, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## CSS Classes\n\n```css\nInfoPanel {\n    width: 200;\n    height: 100%;\n    dock: right;\n    background: $surface;\n    border-left: solid $primary;\n}\n\nInfoPanel .info-header { }\nInfoPanel .info-context { }\nInfoPanel .info-mcp { }\nInfoPanel .info-files { }\nInfoPanel .info-footer { }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Toggle Behavior\n\n- **Ctrl+M** toggles panel visibility\n- Panel state persists during session\n- Auto-shows when terminal width >= 80 columns on startup\n- Auto-hides when terminal shrinks below 80 columns\n\n---\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n1. **Narrow terminal (< 80 cols):** Panel hidden by default\n2. **No MCP servers:** Show \"No MCP servers\" placeholder\n3. **No modified files:** Show \"No files modified\" placeholder\n4. **Long file paths:** Truncate with ellipsis, show full path on hover\n5. **Zero tokens:** Hide context section until first token count received",
